Sentencas: This work studies electrochemical reforming of CH4/CO2 (1:1) in an oxide-ion-conducting solid oxide electrolyzer with perovskite cathode La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3 -aEuro parts per thousand delta (LSCM).
Titulo: Efficient syngas production from methane reforming in solid oxide electrolyser with LSCM cathode loaded with Ni-Cu catalysts

Sentencas: The Ni, Cu, and bimetallic Ni-Cu nanocatalysts are, respectively, loaded to LSCM electrode to enhance electrochemical biogas reforming performances.
Titulo: Efficient syngas production from methane reforming in solid oxide electrolyser with LSCM cathode loaded with Ni-Cu catalysts

Sentencas: The synergetic effect of Ni and Cu produces excellent cathode activity with Faraday efficiency considerably improved by 20 %.
Titulo: Efficient syngas production from methane reforming in solid oxide electrolyser with LSCM cathode loaded with Ni-Cu catalysts
